== Short Bio 
I am a doctoral candidate at Politecnico di Milano, working under supervision of prof. Lorenzo Fagiano. I am particularly interested in non-linear and distributed control, with applications to UAVs and other aerospace systems. I earned a M.Sc. from RWTH Aachen, and have performed research in non-linear and multi-agent control for HVDC power systems. After my M.Sc. I have worked on a radio payload currently onboard the microsatellite Diwata-2.

== News 
- \[2019.08.31\] I have now left the microsatellite development team at UP Diliman to embark on a new and exciting Ph.D. journey at Politecnico! I thank all my mentors and colleagues from this dynamic research group, for a highly productive and impactful work.
- \[2019.08.19\] Our article on wavelet-based protection for HVDC grids is now [https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijepes.2019.105475 online]!
- \[2019.04.26\] We are now announcing Diwata-2 amateur radio as *ready* for worldwide use! Link to UP Media coverage [https://www.up.edu.ph/index.php/surviving-the-big-one-with-diwata-2s-amateur-radio-unit/ here].
- \[2018.10.31\] Diwata-2 is launched to space today! See [https://www.up.edu.ph/index.php/diwata-2-takes-flight/ UP Media coverage].
- \[2018.07.16\] Our article on multi-agent-based frequency control for HVDC grids is [https://doi.org/10.1049/iet-rpg.2018.5120 out].
- \[2018.03.01\] Published [https://doi.org/10.1109/TPWRD.2018.2811560 online] our article on predictive sliding mode control for HVDC grids.

